title: Grateful Dead Live at Knickerbocker Arena on 1991-03-24
lineage: MAD > Sony TCD-D10P > SPDIF > Audiophile  2496 > Wavelab (SRC & Dither) > CD-Wave > TLH > FLAC  1644 Tagged. Taped & transferred by Andrew F. 04/2011
description:
Set 1

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Wang Dang Doodle, Jack A Roe, Beat It On Down The Line, Brown Eyed Women, Desolation Row, Deal

Set 2

Samson & Delilah, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Looks Like Rain-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Standing On the Moon-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
That dreaded S Great tape, thanks. I think taping was at it's peak during these years as DAT and Cd were really picking up speed. Great Job.
Nice "S" on the green ticket ! Mine's got one too. Those stormtroopers in the Knick were marking tickets with an S for smoking, if you weren't in your seat or for anything else that irritated them. Second violation, they dragged you out the door.
Funny thing is , all us S people ended up in the upper deck behind the drums and had a real party...
